race.comment: Keen that a couple of the locals can fight out the finish here. ANGEL TORQUE (3) is one of them and she's built a strong record from only 10 starts. She wasn't far away in some much stronger races last campaign and her recent trial suggests she's ready to go first-up in this grade. DUNREAL (2) is back from a lengthy spell but he's a horse that can progress quickly through the grades. Suspect he'll be better over further but he was a first-up winner last spring. MERCURY EIGHT (4) wasn't beaten far in a stronger race last start. Will go forward and be hard to run down back to this grade. MISS SGHIRRIPA (8) is an each-way chance on the strength of her maiden win, while STEEL TSUNAMI (1) is a likely improver second-up and must be respected.
